<div id="banner">
	<h1>Introducing&#8230; Warchalking! The New Swhack!</h1>
</div>

<div class="content">
<p>Faithful readers have probably been wondering where I&#8217;ve been for the past few days. (You haven&#8217;t? You&#8217;re not very faithful!) </p>

<p>Well, I&#8217;ve been setting up the new <a href="http://www.warchalking.org/">warchalking community site</a>, which I&#8217;m proud to take over from the incredible <a href="http://www.blackbeltjones.com/">Matt Jones</a>. It&#8217;s powered by <a href="http://scoop.kuro5hin.org/">Scoop</a>, the software behind <a href="http://www.kuro5hin.org/">K5</a> and <a href="http://www.infoanarchy.org/">InfoAnarchy</a>. Please stop by and check it out. (<code>www.warchalking.org</code>)</p>

<p>Meanwhile, I&#8217;ve also been deploying <a href="http://notabug.com/swhack/">The New Swhack</a>. It&#8217;s got all the sillyness, tech news and cool  pointers of the old Swhack, with a fresh new design and a cleaner look. We&#8217;re still experimenting with the style but it&#8217;s turning into more of a web diary than a weblog. Instead of a bunch of entries posted, it&#8217;s a new HTML page built every day. And it also includes tons of details about my personal life! (Yes, I know you don&#8217;t care.) Here are the issues you&#8217;ve missed:</p><ul><li><a href="http://www.aaronsw.com/weblog/2002-08-16">2002-08-16</a></li><li><a href="http://www.aaronsw.com/weblog/2002-08-17">2002-08-17</a></li><li><a href="http://www.aaronsw.com/weblog/2002-08-18">2002-08-18</a></li><li><a href="http://www.aaronsw.com/weblog/2002-08-19">2002-08-19</a></li><li><a href="http://www.aaronsw.com/weblog/2002-08-20">2002-08-20</a></li></ul><p>Enjoy! (<code>notabug.com/swhack</code>)</p>

<p class="posted">posted August 20, 2002 10:20 AM (<a class="category" href="http://www.aaronsw.com/weblog/cat_personal">Personal</a>)  <a href="000518" rel="bookmark">#</a></p>
</div>

